<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="88" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d88">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 493.11/497.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Reinsch</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 80.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department acknowledges the receipt
                            of your despatch No. 159 of March 18 and your No. 165 of March 24,
                            regarding claims against the Chinese Government growing out of the
                            revolution of 1911–1912.</p>
                        <p>In the event of the British and German Governments, or either of them,
                            expressing their willingness to refuse definitely to present to China
                            claims for indirect losses, such as are set forth in the summary sent
                            with your No. 165 of certain claims received by the Legation, you are
                            instructed to refuse to present such claims.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cone Johnson</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>